to live the life they want.

419
00:33:43,288 --> 00:33:46,224
But don't you think
it's also what's interesting about it

420
00:33:48,159 --> 00:33:50,128
Interesting? How?

421
00:33:50,395 --> 00:33:53,365
Most of the time,
our wishes don't come true.

422
00:33:53,798 --> 00:33:57,102
When they do,
you'll be particularly happy.

423
00:33:58,904 --> 00:34:00,005
I mean it.

424
00:34:00,505 --> 00:34:01,406
Take now, for instance.

425
00:34:01,473 --> 00:34:03,241
If we come to see the ocean every day,

426
00:34:03,308 --> 00:34:04,976
there wouldn't be anything
special about it.

427
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:07,379
But if we sneak a break
from busy work at times,

428
00:34:07,445 --> 00:34:09,114
we would find the ocean is blue,

429
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:10,548
the wind is comforting,

430
00:34:10,615 --> 00:34:11,983
and our moods are good.

431
00:34:14,052 --> 00:34:15,520
You stir-fried Shancai.

432
00:34:15,587 --> 00:34:16,788
You're a special one.

433
00:34:16,855 --> 00:34:19,357
I am. Since you're always surrounded
by pretty women,

434
00:34:19,424 --> 00:34:21,226
I become special.

435
00:34:21,927 --> 00:34:22,928
Shancai.

436
00:34:22,994 --> 00:34:24,362
You've finally recovered.

437
00:34:24,963 --> 00:34:27,933
I was worried
that you would have a meltdown

438
00:34:27,999 --> 00:34:29,701
because the billboard is off.

439
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:36,207
Daoming Si is living his new life.

440
00:34:36,274 --> 00:34:38,310
How can I not move on?

441
00:34:38,977 --> 00:34:41,780
We never know
what's going to happen tomorrow,

442
00:34:41,947 --> 00:34:44,749
unless we take a big step forward
to take a good look at it.

443
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,919
Welcome your new life, Meizuo.

444
00:34:47,986 --> 00:34:49,154
Go for it.

445
00:34:50,655 --> 00:34:51,957
Yeah.

446
00:34:52,023 --> 00:34:53,191
Go for it.

447
00:34:53,258 --> 00:34:54,659
Go for it...

448
00:34:54,726 --> 00:34:56,361
Go for it!

449
00:34:59,631 --> 00:35:01,266
Go for it!

450
00:35:05,003 --> 00:35:05,870
Eighty-three hundred.

451
00:35:05,937 --> 00:35:07,105
Eighty-four hundred.

452
00:35:07,172 --> 00:35:08,873
What are you doing? I'm counting money.

453
00:35:08,940 --> 00:35:10,041
I was just borrowing.

454
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:11,476
-Eighty-five hundred.
-I got no money.

455
00:35:11,543 --> 00:35:13,111
Eighty-six hundred, eighty-seven hundred.

456
00:35:13,178 --> 00:35:14,312
Eighty-eight hundred.

457
00:35:17,048 --> 00:35:18,249
Don't you guys find it strange?

458
00:35:18,350 --> 00:35:20,185
Last name is Ah. First name is Xing.

459
00:35:20,518 --> 00:35:22,787
And we know nothing else about him.

460
00:35:23,488 --> 00:35:24,489
So strange.

461
00:35:24,990 --> 00:35:26,057
Who cares about his name.

462
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:28,259
How can I hire him
when he can't even fry eggs?

463
00:35:29,394 --> 00:35:30,962
Don't be so mean.

464
00:35:31,029 --> 00:35:34,065
At least he's been cleaning tables
the whole morning

465
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:36,134
and doing dishes afterward, right?

466
00:35:37,002 --> 00:35:38,269
I didn't ask him to.

467
00:35:39,904 --> 00:35:41,640
You're so petty-minded.

468
00:35:41,706 --> 00:35:42,774
Took your gain for granted.

469
00:35:42,907 --> 00:35:44,042
Why be such a penny pincher?

470
00:35:44,242 --> 00:35:46,277
Are you kidding me?
How much do I make per day?

471
00:35:46,344 --> 00:35:47,912
I must pinch my pennies.

472
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:50,849
